                                <li>Enhanced competitive benchmarking</li>
                                <li>Green business evaluation criteria</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="timeline-item">
                        <div class="timeline-content">
                            <h3>Phase 3: Complete Integration</h3>
                            <p>Implement the more complex changes and fully integrate green concepts:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Environmental values in user research</li>
                                <li>Sustainability touchpoints in journey mapping</li>
                                <li>Green innovation brainstorming techniques</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h4>2. Training for Trainers</h4>
                <p>Prepare trainers to effectively facilitate green content:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Knowledge Building:</strong> Ensure trainers understand basic sustainability concepts and local green business examples</li>
                    <li><strong>Practice Sessions:</strong> Allow trainers to practice delivering the new content and responding to questions</li>
                    <li><strong>Resource Library:</strong> Create a collection of Iraqi green business examples and success stories</li>
                    <li><strong>Feedback Loop:</strong> Establish a process for trainers to share what works and what doesn't</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>3. Selective Application</h4>
                <p>Adapt implementation based on each cohort's needs:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Relevance Assessment:</strong> For each cohort, identify which green elements are most relevant to participants' business ideas</li>
                    <li><strong>Participant Interest:</strong> If participants show strong interest in sustainability, go deeper into the concepts</li>
                    <li><strong>Sector Focus:</strong> Emphasize different aspects based on sectors represented in the cohort (e.g., energy efficiency for retail, waste reduction for food businesses)</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>4. Local Examples Database</h4>
                <p>Develop a growing collection of Iraqi green business examples:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Local Success Stories:</strong> Document Iraqi businesses that have successfully implemented green practices</li>
                    <li><strong>Resource Efficiency Examples:</strong> Collect examples of cost savings through smarter resource use</li>
                    <li><strong>Green Innovation:</strong> Highlight innovative Iraqi solutions to environmental challenges</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Opportunities:</strong> Track emerging green market trends in Iraq</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>5. Tool Integration</h4>
                <p>Connect curriculum changes to practical business tools:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Simplified Risk Assessment:</strong> Create a basic version of the Risk Assessment Process for the pre-incubator</li>
                    <li><strong>Business Efficiency Checklist:</strong> Adapt the existing checklist for early-stage entrepreneurs</li>
                    <li><strong>Green Business Canvas:</strong> Develop a version of the Business Model Canvas that includes resource efficiency considerations</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>6. Measurement & Refinement</h4>
                <p>Evaluate the impact of green curriculum elements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Participant Feedback:</strong> Survey participants on the usefulness of green business concepts</li>
                    <li><strong>Business Outcomes:</strong> Track whether participants implement resource efficiency measures in their businesses</li>
                    <li><strong>Curriculum Refinement:</strong> Continuously improve green content based on feedback and outcomes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

