                <p>How to effectively integrate green business concepts while maintaining focus on entrepreneurial fundamentals</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tabs">
                <div class="tab active" onclick="openTab(event, 'business-first')">Business-First Approach</div>
                <div class="tab" onclick="openTab(event, 'integration')">Integration Method</div>
                <div class="tab" onclick="openTab(event, 'practical')">Practical Tools</div>
                <div class="tab" onclick="openTab(event, 'local')">Local Context</div>
            </div>

            <div id="business-first" class="tab-content active">
                <h3>Business-First Approach</h3>
                <p>Frame sustainability as a strategic business advantage with concrete benefits:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk reduction and operational resilience:</strong> Help businesses prepare for resource constraints and market changes</li>
                    <li><strong>Cost efficiency and resource optimization:</strong> Identify opportunities to reduce expenses through smarter resource use</li>
                    <li><strong>Market differentiation and customer loyalty:</strong> Create competitive advantages through green features that customers value</li>
                    <li><strong>Long-term business viability:</strong> Build business models that remain viable despite changing resource availability</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="example-title">Example: Business-First Framing</div>
                    <p><strong>Instead of:</strong> "Reducing energy use helps the environment."</p>
                    <p><strong>Use:</strong> "Reducing energy use cuts operational costs and improves resilience against power outages."</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="integration" class="tab-content">
                <h3>Integration Method</h3>
                <p>Weave green concepts naturally into existing business modules by:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Enhancing examples with efficiency dimensions:</strong> Use examples that show how business decisions impact resource use and costs</li>
                    <li><strong>Adding case studies:</strong> Include Iraqi businesses that demonstrate the alignment between sustainability and profitability</li>
                    <li><strong>Incorporating risk assessment:</strong> Add simple risk assessment components to business planning frameworks</li>
                    <li><strong>Updating facilitator notes:</strong> Provide trainers with discussion prompts about resource efficiency and business resilience</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="example-title">Example: Natural Integration</div>
                    <p><strong>Instead of:</strong> Adding a separate "green business" module</p>
                    <p><strong>Use:</strong> Adding resource efficiency criteria to the existing competitive benchmarking exercise</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="practical" class="tab-content">
                <h3>Practical Tools</h3>
                <p>Supplement modules with concrete decision-making tools:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk & Resilience Assessment:</strong> Simple worksheet to identify business vulnerabilities</li>
                    <li><strong>Business Efficiency Checklist:</strong> Tool to locate cost-saving opportunities</li>
                    <li><strong>"No-Regrets Path" framework:</strong> Approach for customer journey mapping that identifies reliable efficiency gains</li>
                    <li><strong>Value-Aligned Evaluation:</strong> Framework for assessing how sustainability creates customer value</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="example-title">Example: Business Efficiency Checklist</div>
                    <p>The checklist helps entrepreneurs identify efficiency opportunities by asking questions like:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What resources (energy, water, materials) cost your business the most?</li>
                        <li>Which operational processes could be optimized to reduce waste?</li>
                        <li>How would your business adapt if resource costs doubled?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="local" class="tab-content">
                <h3>Local Context</h3>
                <p>Adapt green concepts to Iraqi realities and opportunities:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Energy reliability:</strong> Frame solar adoption as a business resilience strategy against power outages</li>
                    <li><strong>Water conservation:</strong> Position water-efficient processes as cost-saving measures in areas with unreliable water access</li>
                    <li><strong>Local sourcing:</strong> Highlight how local materials reduce transportation costs and supply chain risks</li>
                    <li><strong>Emerging opportunities:</strong> Connect to local sustainability initiatives and businesses</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="example-title">Example: Regional Solar Businesses</div>
                    <p>Solar energy providers in Iraq help businesses reduce their energy costs while providing reliable power during grid outages. This example demonstrates how addressing environmental challenges creates direct business value in the local context.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

