                <h4>2. Training for Trainers</h4>
                <p>Prepare trainers to effectively facilitate the new content:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Knowledge Building:</strong> Ensure trainers understand basic resource efficiency concepts and local examples</li>
                    <li><strong>Practice Sessions:</strong> Allow trainers to practice delivering the new content and responding to questions</li>
                    <li><strong>Resource Library:</strong> Create a collection of local case studies and success stories</li>
                    <li><strong>Feedback Loop:</strong> Establish a process for trainers to share what works and what doesn't</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>3. Selective Application</h4>
                <p>Adapt implementation based on each cohort's needs:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Relevance Assessment:</strong> For each cohort, identify which efficiency elements are most relevant to participants' business ideas</li>
                    <li><strong>Participant Interest:</strong> If participants show strong interest in sustainability, go deeper into the concepts</li>
                    <li><strong>Sector Focus:</strong> Emphasize different aspects based on sectors represented in the cohort (e.g., energy efficiency for retail, waste reduction for food businesses)</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>4. Local Examples Database</h4>
                <p>Develop a growing collection of local business examples:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Local Success Stories:</strong> Document businesses that have successfully implemented resource efficiency measures</li>
                    <li><strong>Resource Efficiency Examples:</strong> Collect examples of cost savings through smarter resource use</li>
                    <li><strong>Supply Chain Innovations:</strong> Highlight examples of businesses improving supply chain resilience</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Opportunities:</strong> Track emerging trends in resource-efficient products and services</li>
                </ul>
